# Dev Scout — chat loop

This repo is a **chat-driven research harness**, not a CLI tool. The user runs the loop in Cursor chat.

## When the user asks to scout, research, run the loop, or get today's jam

1. Read [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) and [docs/CHAT-LOOP.md](docs/CHAT-LOOP.md)
2. Determine the run day (`YYYY-MM-DD`) and work under `runs/YYYY-MM-DD/`
3. Execute the research loop by **writing files** and **using web research tools** — do not tell the user to run terminal commands
4. Use **Cursor web search**, **agent-reach**, and web fetch — never ask for external API keys ([docs/SUBSCRIPTIONS.md](docs/SUBSCRIPTIONS.md))
5. Never write digest or email until judge criteria in `config/judge.yaml` pass
6. Email the findings brief to `DEV_SCOUT_EMAIL` (Resend) when secrets are available; write `06-email/send-result.json`
7. End by pointing the user to `runs/YYYY-MM-DD/06-email/email-draft.md` and the send result

## Jam rules

Every promoted finding needs: `source_url`, `how_to_steps` (≥3), evidence grade A or B, benefit (`speed` / `robustness` / `both`). See `config/jam-criteria.yaml`.

## Resume

If `runs/YYYY-MM-DD/RUN.md` exists, read it and continue from the listed stage.
